Install successfully a virtual machines (VM) Ubuntu on Vbox
With firstly user is "adm1n"
1/2 day	
File management and bash script	
Use Vi and Nano to compose a paragraph at least 15 lines, fast go to an line, fast find a string in the paragraph and create a text file
Grant owner full permission, other read-only
Change file owner
Find files that size are larger 20 MB
Write a bash file to create a text file with name is "<hhmmss>-<DDMMYYYY>.<username>.log", run bash in 1 minute, create 1 file each 5 seconds.
What are the directories in the / file?
1/2 day	


User management	
Config "adm1n" to be able to use "root" privileges without password.
Setup password policy at least 8 characters, complexity required, password expiration on both
Create user "d3v", group "d3v0p5" on both
Configure newly created users so that they do not have the right to switch to other users.
1/2 day	
Clone VM.	
Disable SSH to "adm1n" user.
List VM names so they can be referred to by name.
Clone the above virtual machine into 4 machines A, B, C, D.
1/2 day	
Networking	
Change SSH port on VMs A, B, C, D to 7222, 6222, 5222, 4222 respectively.
Setup SSH client using SuperPuTTY or mRemoteNG or VSCODE from host to each VM.
Configure VMs so they can connect to each other, copy files between them via "VM's name" and "d3v" user with key pair.
1/2 day	
Install package

and config application

Install Tomcat server on machine A by using package, configure it as a service with "d3v" user
Install MySQL 8.0 on machine B, configure it to be accessible from both internal and external sources.
2 days

+ 1/2 day



Process management	
Use command to display process information/kill process, run background process
Write a bash file using loop to print CPU, RAM, DISK information every 20 secs
Write a program to check tomcat server every 2 minutes, if it down then start it
Find process that run on port 3306, kill it then start it again
1 day	


Backup - Log - Crond	
Setup log rotate for tomcat server
Setup a job to run periodically to backup MySQL data every day
1 day	


Configure application	
Configure Tomcat in A so that it can use MySQL in B (Refer: Tomcat JDBC Connection Pool, Link)
Set up Nginx/php on machine C to connect to MySQL in D, show simple to-do item list web page (Refer: Link)
2 days

+ 1/2 day



OpenSSH	
 

Using OpenSSH to forward defined ports (Optional)
Using OpenSSH as a sock proxy (Optional)
 



Network File System	
 

Set up an NFS server and an NFS client. (Optional)
Share a directory from the server with the client and access it from the client. (Optional)
 



